geneVariantDescriptions.description: EGFR C797S lies within the ATP-binding pocket in the protein kinase domain of the Egfr protein (PMID: 25964297). C797S has been demonstrated to confer resistance to third-generation Egfr inhibitors (PMID: 25964297, PMID: 25948633, PMID: 29410323), is enriched in growth factor-independent cells in a high-throughput screening assay, but does not support growth factor-independent proliferation in culture, and results in Egfr phosphorylation upon Egf stimulation to similar levels as wild-type protein in culture (PMID: 30952700), and therefore, its effect on Egfr protein function is unknown.
